doc.after: Dulles's iconic main terminal houses ticketing, baggage claim, U.S. Customs and Border Protection, the Z gates, and other support facilities. The terminal was recognized by the American Institute of Architects in 1966 for its design concept; its roof is a suspended catenary providing a wide enclosed area unimpeded by any columns. It houses ticketing, baggage claim, and information facilities, as well as the International Arrivals Building for passenger processing.
